<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881102-0084 </DOCNO><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides: Preventive Detention? </HL><SO> </SO><TEXT>   Detroit Mayor Coleman Young believes the city may have finally turned the corner in its efforts to contain the wave of arson the city suffers every year at Halloween. The Police Department reported that it detained 452 youths who had violated the city's curfew over the Halloween weekend. We don't know what the civil-liberties lobby would think, but we suspect it's well supported by the citizens of Detroit who still have houses to live in this year. </TEXT></DOC>